Subject: [PATCH] feat(ui): token swap v1 - purple/teal/orange CareLogic-inspired palette

Implements UX retrofit V1 token changes:
- Primary: blue (210 79% 60%) → purple (268 56% 38%) | 9.3:1 contrast with white
- Accent: teal (175 60% 50%) → teal (174 62% 44%) | 7.5:1 contrast with near-black
- CTA: new orange token (27 90% 55%) | 7.2:1 contrast with near-black
- Ring: now uses primary purple for focus outlines
- Radius: tightened tiers (lg/md/sm: 0.75rem/0.5rem/0.25rem)
- Animations: shortened to 150ms for snappier feel

All changes meet WCAG 2.2 AA contrast gates (≥ 4.5:1).
Light mode uses near-black (#111111) on saturated teal/orange.
Dark mode flips to white foreground on those accents.

Related:
- deliverables.md Section 1 (Token Mapping Spec)
- v1-token-diff.json
- contrast-matrix.csv
- tickets.md: STORY-UX-Tokens-Diff, STORY-UX-Header-CTA, STORY-UX-Buttons-Variants

